definitions.definition: The act of forcing sex upon another person without their consent or against their will ; originally coitus forced by a man on a woman, but now generally any sex act forced by any person upon another person; by extension, any non-consensual sex act forced on or perpetrated by any being . [from 15th c.]
( slang , sometimes offensive ) An experience that is pleasant for one party and unpleasant for the other, particularly when the unwilling partner's suffering is worse than necessary.

subdefinitions.definition: (Can we clean up this sense?) An insult to one's senses so severe that one feels that they cannot ever be the same afterwards.
examples: The ear rape of that concert was so bad I can't even listen to their songs at work anymore.

definitions.definition: ( now rare ) The taking of something by force ; seizure , plunder . [from early 14th c.]
( now archaic ) The abduction of a woman, especially for sexual purposes. [from 15th c.]
( obsolete ) That which is snatched away.
( obsolete ) Movement, as in snatching; haste; hurry.
